    "When drug A and drug B are combined, the effect of drug B is modified by the proportion 1 -E A that is \"spared\" by drug A.",
    "By summing up these two terms, i.e., E A and E B 1-E A, we get the expected combined effect E AB.",
    "then it signifies synergism.",
    "If the two values are equal, it suggests additivity, and otherwise, it implies antagonism (Duarte and Vale 2022).",
    "Zero Interaction Potency (ZIP) score is a valuable tool used to assess the synergistic or antagonistic effects of drug combinations."
